gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 107, Kings 89
gameRecap.excerpt: The Rockets defeated the Kings, 107-89 tonight in Houston. Dillon Brooks finished with a team-high 26 points along with 9 rebounds for the Rockets, while Fred VanVleet tallied 21 points, 12 assists and six rebounds in the game. Malik Monk recorded 18 points, seven assists and three rebounds for the Kings. The Rockets improve their record to 2-3 with the win, while the Kings fall to 2-3 for the season.
